{"type":"message","id":"c4c89bf3","parentId":"de183749","timestamp":"2026-03-24T09:23:40.842Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The pulse ran but the LLM returned an empty response, which caused the script to crash when trying to parse the OBSERVATION and MUTATION sections. This is why the errors occurred in pulse.ps1.\n\nThe errors were:\n1. `$llmResponse.IndexOf('### MUTATION')` - can't call method on null (empty response)\n2. `$obsMatch` regex match failed because `$llmResponse` is null\n\nThe pulse completed but without any LLM analysis. This means no observation was generated, no mutations were proposed, and the cycle was essentially a no-op.\n\nThis is a failure state - the LLM didn't respond. This could be due to:\n\n\n- API issue with the LLM endpoint\n- Rate limiting\n- Timeout before response received\n\nI should report this to Zach.","thinkingSignature":"1b8396e85aac099334a6040b0f428d91309d964d90a593c12ebf242f55437e28"},{"type":"text","text":"**Sandbox Pulse — 2026-03-24 05:23 AM**\n\n**Result:** ⚠️ Cycle completed but LLM response was empty.\n\nThe pulse script ran and reached the LLM call, but received a **zero-length response**. This caused two script errors when trying to parse `### OBSERVATION` and `### MUTATION` sections (since there's nothing to parse).\n\n- **Applied mutations:** None — no valid response to extract from\n- **Proposed mutations waiting:** 0\n- **Error type:** `InvalidOperationException` / `MethodInvocationException` — null-valued expressions in `IndexOf()` and `Regex::Match()`\n\n**Likely cause:** API timeout, rate limit, or the model endpoint returned nothing this cycle. The script's error handling doesn't gracefully handle empty LLM responses — it assumes content is present before trying to extract sections.\n\nNot critical (script kept running), but means no observation or mutation work happened this cycle."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","us